'''Kuzbassenergo OAO''' (also known as '''TGK-12''') is a [[Russia]]n [[Joint stock company|joint-stock]] company specialized in the distribution of energy. The company's [[headquarters]] are located in the Russian city of [[Barnaul]], in the [[Altai Krai]] region (Southwest [[Siberia]]). The company is controlled by Siberian Energy Investments Ltd., a holding company controlled by [[Andrey Melnichenko]]'s company Donalink Ltd.<ref name=suek150411>{{cite press release | url= http://www.suek.ru/en/page.php?id=306&article=4139 | title = OJSC SUEK announces intention to demerge its power generation business | publisher = [[Siberian Coal Energy Company|SUEK]] | date=2011-04-15 | accessdate=2012-03-05}}</ref><ref name=reuters250411a>{{cite news | url= https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/KZBGY.PK/key-developments/article/2304118 | title = SUEK OAO Sells Its 50% Stake In Kuzbassenergo OAO-SKRIN | agency = [[Reuters]] | date=2011-04-25 | accessdate=2012-03-05}}</ref><ref name=reuters250411b>{{cite news | url= https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/KZBGY.PK/key-developments/article/2304120 | title = SIBERIAN ENERGY INVESTMENTS LTD Increases Its Stake In Kuzbassenergo OAO-SKRIN | agency = [[Reuters]] | date=2011-04-25 | accessdate=2012-03-05}}</ref>
According to the company's official [[website]], Kuzbassenergo generated 24.906&nbsp;GWh in 2006.<ref>[http://www.kuzbassenergo.ru/eng/company/about/1/activity.php Kuzbassenergo website, Activity]{{failed verification|date=May 2016}}</ref>
Kuzbassenergo's CEO is Sergey Mikhailov. The company was delisted from the [[Moscow Exchange]] in January 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kuzbassenergo OAO to be delisted as of Jan. 20, 2016|url=https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/KZBE.RTS/key-developments/article/3309191|accessdate=18 August 2017|work=Reuters}}</ref>
